description.plain:
Johnathan Michael Porter (b. January 20, 1997), better known by the stage name Blueface, is a rapper from Los Angeles, California. His stage name is a reference to his ties to the School Yard Crip gang as well as the image of Benjamin Franklin tattooed on his right cheek. Ben Frank appears on the $100 bill and the modern version of the bill has a blue strip on it.

Blueface released his first song, “kicc a doe,” in September 2017. He continued an extensive stretch of singles in late 2017 and early 2018, before releasing his debut mixtape, Famous Cryp, on June 20, 2018. He followed this with his second tape, Two Coccy, exactly three months later.

On October 8, 2018, WorldStarHipHop debuted the music video for “Respect My Crypn’,” which quickly became a viral sensation due to Blueface’s bizarre, off-beat flow and high-pitched delivery. Following the music video’s release, some of his other songs, like “Thotiana” and “Next Big Thing,” also started to go viral.

Following his sudden rise to stardom, Blueface signed to Cash Money West in November 2018.

On August 9, 2019, Blueface released Dirt Bag, his debut EP.

On March 13, 2020, Blueface released his debut album, Find the Beat, after numerous delays.

description.plain:
Cardi B’s “Thotiana” is the second official remix of Blueface’s hit single, following YG’s version only three weeks later.

A short snippet of the song was posted to Blueface’s Instagram story on February 6th and featured part of Cardi’s vocals.

https://twitter.com/cardibteam/status/1093140440369516544?s=21

The song was first released as a Cole Bennett-directed music video on February 16, 2019, before hitting streaming services on February 20th.

Genius sat down with Blueface on Dec 10, 2018
for a more in-depth explanation of the track:

“Respect My Cryppin'” is Blueface’s gang-banging breakout single. Through the track, he reps his Crip affiliation hardcore and talks about handling his street beef.
The music video for the track was released on WORLDSTARHIPHOP on October 8, 2018.
